n before use. Arguments parsed by minimist are used to construct commands and file paths without type checking or whitelist validation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \".venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/patchright/driver/package/lib/tools/cli-client/registry.js\",\n      \"line\": 110,\n      \"description\": \"Weak file permissions on daemon directories. Session files created without explicit mode specification (using default umask). Sensitive session data could be readable by other users.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \".venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/patchright/driver/package/lib/tools/cli-client/session.js\",\n      \"line\": 65,\n      \"description\": \"Error handling exposes system paths: Error messages may reveal full filesystem paths to users, aiding reconnaissance attacks.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"riskScore\": 68,\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"**Implement strict session name validation**: Use allowlist for session names (alphanumeric + underscore/hyphen only). Reject any session name with path separators or special characters.\",\n    \"**Use array-based child process spawning**: Replace string-based command construction with array arguments to child_process.spawn() to prevent injection attacks.\",\n    \"**Add socket message authentication**: Implement HMAC-SHA256 signing for all socket messages using a shared secret. Verify signatures before processing commands.\",\n    \"**Restrict daemon directory permissions**: Create daemon directories with mode 0700 (user-only access) using fs.mkdir(path, {mode: 0o700}). Ensure session files have mode 0600.\",\n    \"**Validate all CLI arguments**: Implement schema validation (e.g., joi or zod) for all CLI arguments before using them in file paths or process spawning.\",\n    \"**Disable environment-based instrumentation in production**: Remove or restrict PW_INSTRUMENT_MODULES functionality. Use configuration files in protected directories instead